gr.interamerican.bo2.arch.ext
Interface Cache<C extends Comparable<? super C>>

Type Parameters:
C - Type of entries code.
All Known Implementing Classes:
CacheImpl
public interface Cache<C extends Comparable<? super C>>

Cache caches the values of objects used often and changed rare. List elements are the most frequent objects handled by a cache. Cache Objects are uniquely identified by the pair (typeId, code).

Field Detail

SUBTYPEID_FOR_ALL_TYPE_ENTRIES

static final Long SUBTYPEID_FOR_ALL_TYPE_ENTRIES
The subTypeId value 4627583221L is reserved for the representation of all entries of a type as a sub-type. The code:

Set set = cache.getTypeEntries(typeId);

Has the same result as the code:

Set set = cache.getSubCache(typeId, SUBTYPEID_FOR_ALL_TYPE_ENTRIES);
